parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive engine oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing a loss of power and potentially resulting in accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: oil light illumination on the instrument panel
rapid oil consumption without visible leaks
no dashboard warnings for low oil levels.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Recall Repair Delay and Parts Unavailability
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in recall repair and unavailability of parts can leave vehicles with critical safety issues on the road, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Notification of recall without available parts
inability to repair vehicle due to parts unavailability
delay in recall repair exceeding a reasonable amount of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the high-pressure fuel pump can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, which can lead to accidents, especially if the vehicle stalls in traffic, and can also cause damage to other engine components.
symptoms: The vehicle loses power or stalls
the check engine warning light is illuminated
the vehicle may experience difficulty starting or running rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The denial of warranty coverage can cause financial burdens on vehicle owners, who may be forced to pay for repairs out of pocket, and can also lead to a loss of trust in the manufacturer.
symptoms: the vehicle owner is forced to pay for repairs
the vehicle owner experiences frustration and disappointment with the manufacturer.
